			<sentence id="2.1">Hi_</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Lately i have added new comments plugin to my facebook app.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">What i ve noticed is that not all comments are visible to other users.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">I have my real facebook account and other one that i am using for testing (my and other fb apps) purposes.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">When I added new comment from my test account i haven t get any notice and that comment was visible only from my test account.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">When I added new comment from my real account (comment plugin admin)_ that post was visible to everyone.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">To reproduce this bug i have created page with example - http://www.fb.purplestone.pl</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.2">Steps:</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.3">1 Creat new application</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.4">2 My app settings:</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.5">Site URL: http://www.fb.purplestone.pl/</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.6">Site Domain: purplestone.pl</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.7">Canvas Page: http://apps.facebook.com/commentsplugintest/</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.8">Canvar URL: http://www.fb.purplestone.pl/</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.9">3 Create index.php file with comment plugin (an attachement)</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.10">4 Create new facebook account</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">My next steps:</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.2">1 Log in to the new account</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.3">2 Add new comment on http://www.fb.purplestone.pl/  Test  (post to Facebook checked)</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.4">3 Add new comment on http://www.fb.purplestone.pl/  Test2  (post to Facebook unchecked)</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.5">4 Open new browser and log in to facebook to my real account (app and comment box admin)</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.6">5 I ve got no notices_ and no comments on http://www.fb.purplestone.pl/</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">Only if comment was added by my friend or friend of friend i could see it.</sentence>
			<sentence id="8.2">(But i ain t get notice).</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="9">
			<sentence id="9.1">Other example: person A writes a comment_ then person B writes comment.</sentence>
			<sentence id="9.2">If person A is friend of person B_ they can see theirs comments_ but still I (admin) get no notice and cant  see them (comments).</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="10">
			<sentence id="10.1">If I add new comment_ then other users can see it_ and when they reply to it I get notice and can see all replies (even if it was posted no from my friend)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
